Class MessageCommands

java.lang.Object
  edu.umn.cs.dccn.proj1.util.MessageCommands

public class MessageCommands
extends Object

Holds constant strings that are basically shared command messages between server and peers.

Author:
Vivek

Field Summary
static String BYE_NEIGHBOUR
          Peer informing its neighbours that it is quitting.
static String FILE_START
          Sent by a source peer to the destination peer informing them about the start of a file
static String LOOKUP_COMMAND
          Sent by peer to its neighbours to perform the lookup service
static String ORIGINAL_REQUESTER
          Sent by a file requesting peer to its neighbour, along with the lookup command, telling them to figure out the IP (as we don't know the IP for the peer requesting the file)/
static String PEER_NEIGHBOUR_WELCOME
          Sent by a peer to its assigned neighbour to inform them about the assignment
static String PEER_REGISTERED_CONFIRMATION
          Sent by central server to peer as confirmation for the registration process
static String PEER_WANTS_TO_CONNECT
          Sent by Peer to central server while registering
static String PEER_WANTS_TO_DISCONNECT
          Sent by Peer to central server while quitting the network
static String SENDING_ORIGINAL_ADDRESS
          Sent by the central server to let the peer know that it is sending out the peer's IP address as the next message.
